The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Data shield

 Prime Minister Manmohan Singh on Tuesday assured British investors that India has excellent standards for information protection.

 India adheres to all international codes and regulations pertaining to safety and protection of investments and intellectual property rights. We also have in place excellent standards for data protection, he told the India-UK investment summit. 

 The assurance comes after a sting operation by a British TV channel revealed an alleged data theft racket in Indian call centres.




